/ about
%section#about.main.style1.dark.fullscreen
  .content
    %p
      Welcome to
      %br
      %strong Rainforest Tree House
    %p
      Situated at Gunung Pulai in Johor Bahru, you only need 20 minutes to get out of the hustle of the city - back to beautiful nature. Six tree houses, built out of sweat and blood of the owner Ah Yao, sit silently up in trees. 10 min mountain walking distance to the 1st tree house (about 300 stair steps).
      Amenities include: power plug, mosquito net, blanket, cotton pillow, comfortable mattress bathroom with cold stream water shower and toilet bowl.
    %footer
      %a.button.style2.down{:href => "#fee"} More

/ fee
%section#fee.main.style2.right.dark.fullscreen
  .content.box.style2
    %header
      %h2 Fee Included
    %p
      %strong 2D1N:
      1 Dinner (simple vege steamboat), 1 breakfast (nasi lemak)
    %p
      %strong 3D2N:
      2 Dinner, 2 breakfast, 1 lunch
    %p
      %strong Activity included :
      %br
      %i - Briefing of tree house concept (nature building ,organic farming etc )
      %br
      %i - Guide to jungle walk
      %br
      %i - Waterfall (*waterfall trip will be cancel when rainy day or rainy seasons)
    %p.note
      %strong NOTE:
      We can also arrange activities like visit to bee farm + pineapple farm / river trekking + vertical rope drop and earth oven hand on pizza making with optional charge.
    %p.note
      %strong NOTE:
      Check in at about
      %strong 2pm
      and check out at about
      %strong 12 pm
  %a.button.style2.down.anchored{:href => "#things-to-bring"} Next

